The paper deals with the problem of aggregating crowd-sourced annotations for machine learning tasks, which is a common problem in several sub-fields of computer science. The use of Bayesian graphical models and expectation-maximization algorithm suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), natural language processing (cs.CL), computer vision (cs.CV), and human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
